org.corfudb.runtime.clients

Class LayoutClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.corfudb.runtime.clients.LayoutClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IClient

    public class LayoutClient
extends Object
    A client to the layout server.

    The layout client is used by layout servers to initiate a Paxos-based protocol for determining the next layout.

    Created by mwei on 12/9/15.

      • bootstrapLayout

        public CompletableFuture<Boolean> bootstrapLayout(Layout l)
        Bootstraps a layout server.
        Parameters:
        l - The layout to bootstrap with.
        Returns:
        A completable future which will return TRUE if the bootstrap was successful, false otherwise.

      • prepare

        public CompletableFuture<LayoutPrepareResponse> prepare(long epoch,
                                                        long rank)
        Begins phase 1 of a Paxos round with a prepare message.
        Parameters:
        epoch - epoch for which the paxos rounds are being run
        rank - The rank to use for the prepare.
        Returns:
        True, if the prepare was successful. Otherwise, the completableFuture completes exceptionally with OutrankedException.

      • propose

        public CompletableFuture<Boolean> propose(long epoch,
                                          long rank,
                                          Layout layout)
        Begins phase 2 of a Paxos round with a propose message.
        Parameters:
        epoch - epoch for which the paxos rounds are being run
        rank - The rank to use for the propose. It should be the same rank from a successful prepare (phase 1).
        layout - The layout to install for phase 2.
        Returns:
        True, if the propose was successful. Otherwise, the completableFuture completes exceptionally with OutrankedException.

      • committed

        public CompletableFuture<Boolean> committed(long epoch,
                                            Layout layout)
        Informs the server that the proposal (layout) has been committed to a quorum.
        Parameters:
        epoch - epoch affiliated with the layout.
        layout - Layout to be committed.
        Returns:
        True, if the commit was successful.

      • force

        Send a force commit layout request to a layout server
        Parameters:
        layout - the new layout to force commit
        Returns:
        true if it was committed, otherwise false.
